3. MODELING
"The complete radio light curves of PTF11qcj are shown
in Figure 2. These include the latest flux measurements
(integrated fluxes from Tables 1 and 2) along with data
published in Corsi et al. (2016) and Palliyaguru et al.
(2019). Hereafter, we discuss the possible interpretation
of these light curves within the the standard synchrotron
self-absorption (SSA) scenario for radio SNe (see Soder-
berg et al. 2005, and references therein). We also consider
an alternative interpretation within an SSA (first radio
light curve peak) plus off-axis GRB (second radio light
curve peak) scenario. Finally, we discuss the direct size
constraints obtained via our VLBI observations in the
context of both these scenarios."
